commit.message: Fix ring unit test when mlock() is unavailable
Update NEWS
Fix library current_version on MacOS

Fix nullability annotations for zix_canonical_path() and friends

These functions can (and likely will) fail due to filesystem operations
failing, rather than a (rare) failed allocation, so they should be nullable so
clang can find potential null dereferences.
Fix warnings in strict MinGW build
Fix strict build with C11
Test zix_copy_file() in Wasm

Avoid fdatasync() on Darwin

This isn't present at all on (older?) literal Darwin, and additionally fsync()
there doesn't actually flush writes to storage like it does on Linux.  So, use
F_FULLFSYNC which was invented as an alternative API to do this.

Remove unnecessary forward declaration

Looks like include-what-you-use has gotten smarter.

Fix meson.build formatting again

I'll get used to this any day now.
Clean up sphinx build commands
Fix meson.build formatting

Explicitly specify all documentation dependencies

Yet another attempt to sort out flaky documentation builds.  This tries to be
careful and describe the complete documentation dependency graph to meson
explicitly (ignoring tool outputs that aren't used).

Format meson.build files with muon

The less time wasted with manual code formatting, the better.
Improve test suite code coverage

Avoid type conversions

Rework arithmetic slightly to avoid some type conversions, and warnings with
clang-tidy 16.0.6.  Also consistently use explicitly unsigned literals where
appropriate to minimize unsigned/signed conversions in general.
Use anonymous namespace in C++ test

Remove unnecessary includes and forward declarations

According to include-what-you-use 0.20 (7301b1f) based on clang 16.0.6.
